revision.text:
{{one source|date=May 2016}}
A '''culmicole''' is an [[organism]] that lives on the apexes of [[grass]] [[leaves]] and stems. An example of a culmicole are [[species]] of [[planthopper]]s, which spend their lives perched on grass blades. The name was first coined by Lincoln et al. in 1985.<ref>{{cite book| title=Animal Behavior Desk Reference: A Dictionary of Animal Behavior, Ecology, and Evolution| last=Barrows| first=Edward| year=2001| publisher=CRC Press| page=120}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=The Aldrich Dictionary of Phobias and Other Word Families|first=Chris|last=Aldrich|publisher=Trafford Publishing|date=2012|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=A7iDw172KBcC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false|page=18|isbn=9781553698869}}{{Self-published inline|certain=yes|date=January 2018}}</ref>

