A '''sacicolous lichen''' is a [[lichen]] that grows on rock.<ref name=ASLGPZ>[http://www.lichens.lastdragon.org/faq/glossary3.html Alan Silverside's Lichen Glossary (p-z), Alan Silverside]</ref> The prefix "sax" means "rock" or "stone".{{citation needed|date=September 2014}}

